set paths and filenames

### files
long_table=sprintf("%s/data/mp142_TGVG1.1_MPA4_combined_abundance_table_longform1.tsv", find_rstudio_root_file())
metadata_table=sprintf("%s/data/some_teddy_MP142_metadata2.all_samples1.delivery.csv", find_rstudio_root_file())

load long table and metadata

long_dt <- fread(sprintf("%s", long_table), sep = "\t", header = T) %>%
  select(sampleID, rel_abundance, lineage) %>%
  mutate(kingdom = case_when(grepl("k__Bac", lineage) ~ "Bacteria", 
                             grepl("k__Vir", lineage) ~ "Virus",
                             grepl("k__Ar", lineage) ~ "Archea",
                             grepl("k__Euk", lineage) ~ "Eukaryota",
                             TRUE ~ "other"),
         sampleID = as.character(sampleID)) %>%
  filter(kingdom == "Virus" | kingdom == "Bacteria")

meta_dt <- fread(sprintf("%s", metadata_table), sep = ",", header = T) %>%
  select(-V1) %>%
  mutate(sample = as.character(sample))

merge tables and parse for # samples, unique virus and bacterial SGBs

subject_samples_dt <- merge_dt %>%
  group_by(mask_id) %>%
  summarize(total_samples = n_distinct)

plot detected taxa by # of samples

wide_unique_dt %>% ggplot() +
  geom_linerange(aes(x = total_samples_Virus, ymin = distinct_taxa_Bacteria, ymax = distinct_taxa_Virus), color="#D3DDDC", alpha=0.2) +
  geom_point(aes(x = total_samples_Virus, y = distinct_taxa_Virus, color = "#5BBCD6"), alpha=0.6, stroke=0, size=1.5) +
  geom_point(aes(x = total_samples_Virus, y = distinct_taxa_Bacteria, color = "#F2AD00"), alpha=0.6, stroke=0, size=1.5) +
  theme_bw() +
  ylab("SGBs observed") +
  xlab("Number of Longitudinal Samples") +
  scale_colour_manual(name = 'SGB type', values =c('#5BBCD6'='#5BBCD6', '#F2AD00'='#F2AD00'), labels = c('Virus','Bacteria')) +
  theme(panel.grid.major = element_blank(), panel.grid.minor = element_blank())
